he back as it was supposed to appear with this information weâ€™ve only discovered there are a handful of these but weâ€™ll probably never know the exact quantity this means both the interior and the cover were printed independently of other editions with these anomalies making this the true first printing the first printing of this book is just over  copies this would include the anomaly printing according to my publisher source direct from simon and schuster again no information of how many anomaly copies were printed before they caught the mistake but it couldnt have been many as i publish this in early december the publisher informed us that charlie the choochoo has just gone into a third printing title page  fourth edition information the title page of this book reads fourth edition  this is a tongueincheek nod an inside joke from stephen king and the publisher making this edition appear to be a reprint from an older release decades ago even the pages and the book have been made to have an antique look to it it indeed is not a fourth edition it is a first edition the only edition printed and a first printing as long as the copyright page begins with a  in the number line see above please note that it can be a first edition with later printings which begin with the lowest number on the line as in   this would be a second printing etc if you reprint a book maybe a new cover a new introduction etc then this would constitue a second edition but would still have a first printing like any new print run however the current edition is the only version ever published  dave hinchberger proprieter stephen king catalog the overlook connection november  overlookconnectioncom Â Â Â Â Â stephenkingcatalogcom Â  Â shopping cart  items Â sign in password forgottencreate an account Â latest news lawnmower man portfolio is amazing mr mercedes cover art now in stephen king mr mercedes glenn chadbournearrived joyland chabourne foil hardcover joyland librarybound special order by st